result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.
result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. James Ryan Wehrman

defendant.name: Wehrman, James Ryan
defendant.address: N9791 Stinnett Landing Rd, Hayward, WI 54843

records.addlTxt: 10:13 AM Defendant James Ryan Wehrman appeared by video, in custody appears from Sawyer County Jail.  Attorney Jennifer Gross in court for State of Wisconsin.  Court calls case and recites appearances.  Court reviews the extradition complaint.  Court has discussion with DEF, about right to have attorney.   DEF agrees to move forward without attorney.    DEF agrees he is the person Pine County, MN is looking for.   Court advised him as to his right to waive or contest extradition.  Court goes through Waiver of Extradition with DEF.    DEF waives extradition.  Court finds DEF has freely waived his right of extradition - signs document through video conference and DEF remain in custody to await transport to MN.
